<kml>

<concept name=Hold>
<superconcept name=Obstruct>

<hr>
<h3>Component Semantics:</h3>
<component tag=Hold>
  <definition>control movement of</definition>
  <requiredslot name=object>
    <restriction>a Tangible-Entity</restriction>
  </requiredslot>
  <requiredslot name=agent>
    <restriction>holds <slot>object</slot></restriction>
  </requiredslot>
  <requiredslot name=post-conditions>
    <restriction><slot>object</slot> is the <slot>object</slot> of a
      <conceptref name=Be-Held> state whose <slot>agent</slot> is the
      <slot>agent</slot> of the Hold</restriction>
  </requiredslot> 
  <wnsynsets><verb>hold#3, hold#16
  </verb></wnsynsets>
  <wnsynsets><verb>hold_up#1, support#4, sustain#5, take_hold#2
  </verb></wnsynsets>
</component>

<musing>
Hold puts an <slot>object</slot> into a <conceptref name=Be-Held> state.
<conceptref name=Let-Go-Of> takes the <slot>object</slot> out of the
<conceptref name=Be-Held> state. Unlike the other 
<conceptref name=Be-Obstructed> states, <conceptref name=Be-Held> has
an <slot>agent</slot>, the <slot>agent</slot> of Hold. Any
<conceptref name=Move> of an <slot>object</slot> in a
<conceptref name=Be-Held> state must be by the <slot>agent</slot> of the
<conceptref name=Be-Held> and only this <slot>agent</slot> can
<conceptref name=Let-Go-Of> the <slot>object</slot>.
</musing>

